race.comment: Another good race here with LUANA MISS (11) going on top after an impressive victory in the Prelude here a fortnight ago. She was very strong late in the race so 1200m won't be an issue. Maps for a lovely run once again under O'Donnell and she can notch up back-to-back wins. SNITZALATTE (12) looked the winner of the Belgravia Stakes before being gunned down by King Of Light on the post. The form out of that race has been very good and she jumped favourite in that race. Drawn ideally again today and is sure to make her presence felt. TWISTED STEEL (4) showed good improvement last start in the Prelude when only 1.8L off the winner. The wide draw is a niggle, but he's still an improving type and he can put his best foot forward once again. ROSTISLAV (8) is better than he showed last time out and can improve with an inside draw. YES QUEEN (13) gets the winkers back on today and can finish closer.
